descr: "A Map of relationships between 2 structures that can be used to transform data."

fields.name: resourceType
fields.descr: "This is a StructureMap resource"

fields.name: url
fields.descr: "An absolute URI that is used to identify this structure map when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance. This SHALL be a URL, SHOULD be globally unique, and SHOULD be an address at which this structure map is (or will be) published. The URL SHOULD include the major version of the structure map. For more information see [Technical and Business Versions](resource.html#versions)."

fields.name: _url
fields.descr: "Extensions for url"

fields.name: identifier
fields.descr: "A formal identifier that is used to identify this structure map when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance."

fields.name: version
fields.descr: "The identifier that is used to identify this version of the structure map when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or instance. This is an arbitrary value managed by the structure map author and is not expected to be globally unique. For example, it might be a timestamp (e.g. yyyymmdd) if a managed version is not available. There is also no expectation that versions can be placed in a lexicographical sequence."

fields.name: _version
fields.descr: "Extensions for version"

fields.name: name
fields.descr: "A natural language name identifying the structure map. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation."

fields.name: _name
fields.descr: "Extensions for name"

fields.name: title
fields.descr: "A short, descriptive, user-friendly title for the structure map."

fields.name: _title
fields.descr: "Extensions for title"

fields.name: status
fields.descr: "The status of this structure map. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content."

fields.name: _status
fields.descr: "Extensions for status"

fields.name: experimental
fields.descr: "A boolean value to indicate that this structure map is authored for testing purposes (or education/evaluation/marketing), and is not intended to be used for genuine usage."

fields.name: _experimental
fields.descr: "Extensions for experimental"

fields.name: date
fields.descr: "The date  (and optionally time) when the structure map was published. The date must change if and when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the structure map changes."

fields.name: _date
fields.descr: "Extensions for date"

fields.name: publisher
fields.descr: "The name of the individual or organization that published the structure map."

fields.name: _publisher
fields.descr: "Extensions for publisher"

fields.name: contact
fields.descr: "Contact details to assist a user in finding and communicating with the publisher."

fields.name: description
fields.descr: "A free text natural language description of the structure map from a consumer's perspective."

fields.name: _description
fields.descr: "Extensions for description"

fields.name: useContext
fields.descr: "The content was developed with a focus and intent of supporting the contexts that are listed. These terms may be used to assist with indexing and searching for appropriate structure map instances."

fields.name: jurisdiction
fields.descr: "A legal or geographic region in which the structure map is intended to be used."

fields.name: purpose
fields.descr: "Explaination of why this structure map is needed and why it has been designed as it has."

fields.name: _purpose
fields.descr: "Extensions for purpose"

fields.name: copyright
fields.descr: "A copyright statement relating to the structure map and/or its contents. Copyright statements are generally legal restrictions on the use and publishing of the structure map."

fields.name: _copyright
fields.descr: "Extensions for copyright"

fields.name: structure
fields.descr: "A structure definition used by this map. The structure definition may describe instances that are converted, or the instances that are produced."

fields.name: FHIRimport
fields.descr: "Other maps used by this map (canonical URLs)."

fields.name: _import
fields.descr: "Extensions for import"

fields.name: group
